 By Olasunkanmi Akoni Lagos State Governor, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu, has described the All Progressives Congress (APC) victories in Bayelsa and Kogi states, respectively, as an affirmation of the acceptance of APC across the country. Congratulating Mr. David Lyon for his historic victory of defeating his Peoples Democratic Party counterpart after the party had ruled Bayelsa State since the country’s return to democracy in 1999, Sanwo-Olu in statement, Monday, through the Commissioner for Information and Strategy, Gbenga Omotoso, said, “The victory of our party’s candidates in Bayelsa and Kogi is a testimony to the acceptance of the President Muhammadu Buhari administration’s reforms and APC’s progressive actions.” He thanked all stakeholders who made it possible to unseat a political party that had continuously superintended over Bayelsa for two decades. Continue reading Bayelsa, Kogi results, affirmation of acceptance of APC across Nigeria― Sanwo-Olu at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard LEADERSHIP: Chief Lanre Razak, a stalwart of the All Progressives Congress (APC), has congratulated Lagos State governor-elect, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu, on his victory, describing it as well deserved. Razak, popularly known as KLM, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Epe on Monday that Sanwo-oluâ€™s victory was a demonstration… March 11, 2019 In "News" <h1>The Lagos State governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Jimi Agbaje, has conceded defeat to Babajide Sanwo-Olu, who won the March 9 governorship election.</h1> <p class="">Even though the election had been expected to be a close contest between the two, Sanwo-Olu, the candidate of the <strong>All Progressives Congress… March 10, 2019 In "News" He made the pledge at Ikeja while speaking during a â€˜Thank Youâ€™ visit to party members in the Lagos West senatorial zone. The governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Lagos, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu, on Saturday said he would run a government bas